2026-04-16 07:52:40 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 1 Power Flow Indicator LED', 'Control Module 1 Power Flow Indicator Resistor', 'Control Module 2 Power Flow Indicator LED', 'Control Module 2 Power Flow Indicator Resistor'] hypothesis_explanation='Both the Power Flow Indicator LEDs and their series resistors in Control Modules 1 and 2 have been physically removed from the circuit. As per the circuit design, the indicator LED/resistor branches are not in parallel to the load path—they are in parallel to the switches. The removal of these components leaves an open circuit at those points, breaking the series path required for current to reach subsequent modules (and ultimately the lamp). This open circuit in either module will prevent the downstream modules and the load (lamp) from being energized, explaining both the lack of LED activity in all modules and the non-functioning lamp. Restoring the missing indicator LEDs and resistors, or bridging the open connections where they were removed, should restore function.'
